{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make it mandatory for all food outlets/restaurants to offer gluten free options",
        "additional_details": "For individuals living with coeliac disease, gluten intolerance, or other health conditions requiring a gluten-free diet, access to safe food is not a lifestyle preference\u2014it is a medical necessity. Even small amounts of gluten can cause serious health consequences, making it essential that suitable alternatives are widely available.",
        "background": "We call for:\r\n1. At least three clearly labelled gluten-free option on every menu.\r\n2. Staff training on gluten-free preparation and cross-contamination prevention.\r\n3. Transparent ingredient labelling for all menu items.\r\n4. Commitment to inclusivity for people with dietary restrictions.",
